{% extends 'public/base.html.twig' %}

{% block title %}Privacy Policy - GDPR & RODO Compliance - LARPilot{% endblock %}

{% block body %}
{% include 'includes/page_header.html.twig' with {
    title: 'Privacy Policy',
    subtitle: 'GDPR & RODO Compliance - How we protect your data',
    icon: 'bi bi-shield-lock'
} %}

<div class="container mb-5">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-10 mx-auto">
            <p class="text-muted mb-4">
                <strong>Last updated:</strong> {{ "now"|date("F d, Y") }}
            </p>

            <div class="card mb-4">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h2 class="h4 mb-3">1. Introduction</h2>
                    <p>
                        This Privacy Policy describes how LARPilot ("we," "us," or "our") collects, uses, and protects your personal data
                        when you use our platform. We are committed to protecting your privacy and complying with the General Data Protection
                        Regulation (GDPR) and the Polish implementation of GDPR known as RODO (Rozporządzenie o Ochronie Danych Osobowych).
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        By using LARPilot, you consent to the data practices described in this policy.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card mb-4">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h2 class="h4 mb-3">2. Data Controller Information</h2>
                    <p>
                        The data controller responsible for your personal data is:<br>
                        <strong>LARPilot</strong><br>
                        Email: <a href="mailto:admin@larpilot.com">admin@larpilot.com</a>
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        For any questions regarding the processing of your personal data or to exercise your rights under GDPR/RODO,
                        please contact us at the email address above.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card mb-4">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h2 class="h4 mb-3">3. What Data We Collect</h2>
                    <p>We collect and process the following categories of personal data:</p>

                    <h5 class="mt-4">3.1 Account Information</h5>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Name and surname</li>
                        <li>Email address</li>
                        <li>Profile picture (if provided via OAuth)</li>
                        <li>OAuth provider account ID (Google, Facebook, or Discord)</li>
                        <li>Login and authentication credentials</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h5 class="mt-4">3.2 LARP-Related Data</h5>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Character information and descriptions</li>
                        <li>Story objects (threads, quests, events, factions, items, places, relations)</li>
                        <li>Application data for LARP events</li>
                        <li>Participant information and roles</li>
                        <li>Event scheduling and attendance data</li>
                        <li>Comments and interactions on story elements</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h5 class="mt-4">3.3 Technical Data</h5>
                    <ul>
                        <li>IP address</li>
                        <li>Browser type and version</li>
                        <li>Device information</li>
                        <li>Access times and dates</li>
                        <li>Pages visited and actions taken</li>
                        <li>Session information</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h5 class="mt-4">3.4 Location Data</h5>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Event location information (address, city, country, coordinates)</li>
                        <li>Geographic data related to LARP events</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h5 class="mt-4">3.5 Communication Data</h5>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Feedback and support messages</li>
                        <li>Incident reports</li>
                        <li>Email communications</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card mb-4">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h2 class="h4 mb-3">4. Legal Basis for Processing (GDPR Article 6)</h2>
                    <p>We process your personal data based on the following legal grounds:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Consent (Article 6(1)(a)):</strong> You have given explicit consent for us to process your personal data for specific purposes, such as creating an account and participating in LARP events.</li>
                        <li><strong>Contract Performance (Article 6(1)(b)):</strong> Processing is necessary to provide the services you requested, including event management, character creation, and application processing.</li>
                        <li><strong>Legal Obligation (Article 6(1)(c)):</strong> Processing may be required to comply with legal obligations, such as data retention laws or responding to lawful requests from authorities.</li>
                        <li><strong>Legitimate Interests (Article 6(1)(f)):</strong> Processing is necessary for our legitimate interests, such as improving our services, preventing fraud, and ensuring platform security, provided these interests do not override your fundamental rights.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card mb-4">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h2 class="h4 mb-3">5. How We Use Your Data</h2>
                    <p>We use your personal data for the following purposes:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Creating and managing your user account</li>
                        <li>Authenticating your identity via OAuth providers (Google, Facebook, Discord)</li>
                        <li>Facilitating LARP event creation, management, and participation</li>
                        <li>Processing character applications and matching players to characters</li>
                        <li>Managing story elements and narrative content</li>
                        <li>Sending notifications about events, applications, and system updates</li>
                        <li>Integrating with Google services (Sheets, Docs, Calendar) for event management</li>
                        <li>Generating reports and analytics to improve our services</li>
                        <li>Responding to support requests and feedback</li>
                        <li>Preventing fraud, abuse, and security incidents</li>
                        <li>Complying with legal obligations</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card mb-4">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h2 class="h4 mb-3">6. Data Sharing and Third Parties</h2>
                    <p>We may share your personal data with the following third parties:</p>

                    <h5 class="mt-4">6.1 OAuth Providers</h5>
                    <p>
                        We use OAuth authentication through Google, Facebook, and Discord. When you authenticate,
                        these providers share basic profile information (name, email, profile picture) with us.
                        Please review the privacy policies of these providers:
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Privacy Policy</a></li>
                        <li><a href="https://www.facebook.com/privacy/policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Facebook Privacy Policy</a></li>
                        <li><a href="https://discord.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Discord Privacy Policy</a></li>
                    </ul>

                    <h5 class="mt-4">6.2 Google Services Integration</h5>
                    <p>
                        We integrate with Google Sheets, Google Docs, and Google Calendar for event management features.
                        When you use these integrations, data is shared with Google in accordance with their privacy policies.
                    </p>

                    <h5 class="mt-4">6.3 Google Maps API</h5>
                    <p>
                        We use Google Places API for location autocomplete features. When you enter location information,
                        this data is processed by Google to provide address suggestions.
                    </p>

                    <h5 class="mt-4">6.4 Service Providers</h5>
                    <p>
                        We may share data with service providers who assist us in operating our platform, such as:
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Hosting and infrastructure providers</li>
                        <li>Database management services</li>
                        <li>Email delivery services</li>
                        <li>Analytics and monitoring tools</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>
                        These providers are contractually obligated to protect your data and use it only for the purposes we specify.
                    </p>

                    <h5 class="mt-4">6.5 Event Organizers and Participants</h5>
                    <p>
                        When you participate in a LARP event, your data (name, character information, application details)
                        is shared with the event organizers and other participants as necessary for the event's operation.
                    </p>

                    <h5 class="mt-4">6.6 Legal Requirements</h5>
                    <p>
                        We may disclose your data if required by law, court order, or regulatory authority, or to protect
                        our rights, property, or safety, or that of others.
                    </p>

                    <h5 class="mt-4">6.7 Data Transfers Outside EEA</h5>
                    <p>
                        Some of our service providers may be located outside the European Economic Area (EEA). When we transfer
                        data outside the EEA, we ensure appropriate safeguards are in place, such as:
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Standard Contractual Clauses (SCCs) approved by the European Commission</li>
                        <li>Adequacy decisions by the European Commission</li>
                        <li>Privacy Shield or equivalent frameworks (where applicable)</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card mb-4">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h2 class="h4 mb-3">7. Data Retention</h2>
                    <p>
                        We retain your personal data only for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this policy,
                        unless a longer retention period is required or permitted by law.
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Account Data:</strong> Retained while your account is active and for up to 2 years after account closure, unless you request deletion sooner.</li>
                        <li><strong>LARP Event Data:</strong> Retained for the duration of the event and up to 5 years after the event concludes for archival purposes.</li>
                        <li><strong>Technical Logs:</strong> Retained for up to 12 months for security and operational purposes.</li>
                        <li><strong>Legal Compliance:</strong> Data may be retained longer if required by applicable laws or regulations.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>
                        After the retention period expires, we will securely delete or anonymize your personal data.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card mb-4">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h2 class="h4 mb-3">8. Your Rights Under GDPR/RODO</h2>
                    <p>Under GDPR and RODO, you have the following rights regarding your personal data:</p>

                    <h5 class="mt-4">8.1 Right of Access (Article 15)</h5>
                    <p>
                        You have the right to obtain confirmation as to whether your personal data is being processed,
                        and if so, to access your data and receive information about how it is processed.
                    </p>

                    <h5 class="mt-4">8.2 Right to Rectification (Article 16)</h5>
                    <p>
                        You have the right to request correction of inaccurate or incomplete personal data.
                    </p>

                    <h5 class="mt-4">8.3 Right to Erasure / "Right to be Forgotten" (Article 17)</h5>
                    <p>
                        You have the right to request deletion of your personal data under certain circumstances, such as:
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>The data is no longer necessary for the purposes it was collected</li>
                        <li>You withdraw consent and there is no other legal basis for processing</li>
                        <li>You object to processing and there are no overriding legitimate grounds</li>
                        <li>The data has been unlawfully processed</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h5 class="mt-4">8.4 Right to Restriction of Processing (Article 18)</h5>
                    <p>
                        You have the right to request restriction of processing in certain situations, such as when
                        you contest the accuracy of the data or object to processing.
                    </p>

                    <h5 class="mt-4">8.5 Right to Data Portability (Article 20)</h5>
                    <p>
                        You have the right to receive your personal data in a structured, commonly used, machine-readable format
                        and to transmit that data to another controller.
                    </p>

                    <h5 class="mt-4">8.6 Right to Object (Article 21)</h5>
                    <p>
                        You have the right to object to processing of your personal data based on legitimate interests or for
                        direct marketing purposes.
                    </p>

                    <h5 class="mt-4">8.7 Right Not to be Subject to Automated Decision-Making (Article 22)</h5>
                    <p>
                        You have the right not to be subject to decisions based solely on automated processing, including profiling,
                        which produces legal effects or similarly significantly affects you.
                    </p>

                    <h5 class="mt-4">8.8 Right to Withdraw Consent</h5>
                    <p>
                        If processing is based on consent, you have the right to withdraw consent at any time without affecting
                        the lawfulness of processing based on consent before its withdrawal.
                    </p>

                    <h5 class="mt-4">8.9 Right to Lodge a Complaint</h5>
                    <p>
                        You have the right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority:
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Poland (PUODO):</strong> Urząd Ochrony Danych Osobowych<br>
                            ul. Stawki 2, 00-193 Warszawa<br>
                            Phone: +48 22 531 03 00<br>
                            Website: <a href="https://uodo.gov.pl" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">uodo.gov.pl</a>
                        </li>
                        <li><strong>EU Supervisory Authorities:</strong>
                            <a href="https://edpb.europa.eu/about-edpb/board/members_en" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">List of EU Data Protection Authorities</a>
                        </li>
                    </ul>

                    <h5 class="mt-4">How to Exercise Your Rights</h5>
                    <p>
                        To exercise any of these rights, please contact us at
                        <a href="mailto:admin@larpilot.com">admin@larpilot.com</a>.
                        We will respond to your request within 30 days as required by GDPR/RODO.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card mb-4">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h2 class="h4 mb-3">9. Data Security</h2>
                    <p>
                        We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your personal data against
                        unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. These measures include:
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Encryption of data in transit (HTTPS/TLS)</li>
                        <li>Secure password storage using industry-standard hashing algorithms</li>
                        <li>OAuth2 authentication for secure login</li>
                        <li>Access controls and authentication mechanisms</li>
                        <li>Regular security assessments and updates</li>
                        <li>Database backups and disaster recovery procedures</li>
                        <li>Logging and monitoring of system access</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>
                        However, no method of transmission over the Internet or electronic storage is 100% secure.
                        While we strive to protect your data, we cannot guarantee absolute security.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card mb-4">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h2 class="h4 mb-3">10. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
                    <p>
                        We use cookies and similar tracking technologies to enhance your experience on our platform:
                    </p>

                    <h5 class="mt-4">10.1 Essential Cookies</h5>
                    <p>
                        These cookies are necessary for the platform to function properly. They enable core functionality
                        such as security, session management, and authentication. These cannot be disabled.
                    </p>

                    <h5 class="mt-4">10.2 Preference Cookies</h5>
                    <p>
                        These cookies remember your preferences and settings, such as language selection and display preferences.
                    </p>

                    <h5 class="mt-4">10.3 Session Storage</h5>
                    <p>
                        We use session storage to maintain your logged-in state and temporary data during your browsing session.
                    </p>

                    <h5 class="mt-4">10.4 Third-Party Cookies</h5>
                    <p>
                        When you use OAuth authentication or Google services integration, third-party cookies from these
                        providers may be set. Please refer to their respective privacy policies for information about these cookies.
                    </p>

                    <h5 class="mt-4">Managing Cookies</h5>
                    <p>
                        You can control and manage cookies through your browser settings. However, disabling cookies may
                        affect the functionality of our platform.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card mb-4">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h2 class="h4 mb-3">11. Children's Privacy</h2>
                    <p>
                        Our platform is not intended for children under the age of 16 (or the applicable age of digital consent
                        in your jurisdiction). We do not knowingly collect personal data from children under this age.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        If you are a parent or guardian and believe your child has provided us with personal data without your
                        consent, please contact us immediately at <a href="mailto:admin@larpilot.com">admin@larpilot.com</a>,
                        and we will take steps to delete such data.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        For users in Poland: In accordance with Polish regulations, users under 16 years of age must have parental
                        or guardian consent to use our services.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card mb-4">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h2 class="h4 mb-3">12. Data Breach Notification</h2>
                    <p>
                        In the event of a personal data breach that is likely to result in a risk to your rights and freedoms,
                        we will:
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Notify the relevant supervisory authority within 72 hours of becoming aware of the breach (as required by GDPR Article 33)</li>
                        <li>Notify affected users without undue delay if the breach is likely to result in a high risk to their rights and freedoms (as required by GDPR Article 34)</li>
                        <li>Document all data breaches, including the facts, effects, and remedial actions taken</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card mb-4">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h2 class="h4 mb-3">13. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
                    <p>
                        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices, legal requirements,
                        or operational needs. When we make significant changes, we will:
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Update the "Last updated" date at the top of this policy</li>
                        <li>Notify you via email or prominent notice on our platform</li>
                        <li>Where required, obtain your consent for material changes</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>
                        We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically to stay informed about how we protect your data.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card mb-4">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h2 class="h4 mb-3">14. International Users</h2>
                    <p>
                        LARPilot is operated from the European Union and complies with EU/EEA data protection laws.
                        If you are accessing our services from outside the EU/EEA, please be aware that your data may be
                        transferred to, stored, and processed in the EU/EEA.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        By using our services, you consent to the transfer of your data to the EU/EEA and the application
                        of EU/EEA data protection laws.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card mb-4">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h2 class="h4 mb-3">15. Contact Information</h2>
                    <p>
                        If you have any questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy or our data practices,
                        please contact us:
                    </p>
                    <ul class="list-unstyled">
                        <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:admin@larpilot.com">admin@larpilot.com</a></li>
                        <li><strong>Data Protection Officer:</strong> Available upon request</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>
                        For exercising your GDPR/RODO rights, please specify which right you wish to exercise and provide
                        sufficient information for us to verify your identity.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card mb-4">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h2 class="h4 mb-3">16. Specific Information for Polish Users (RODO)</h2>
                    <p>
                        Dla użytkowników w Polsce / For users in Poland:
                    </p>

                    <h5 class="mt-4">Administrator Danych / Data Controller</h5>
                    <p>
                        Administratorem Państwa danych osobowych jest LARPilot. W sprawach dotyczących ochrony danych osobowych
                        prosimy o kontakt: <a href="mailto:admin@larpilot.com">admin@larpilot.com</a>
                    </p>

                    <h5 class="mt-4">Prawa Użytkowników / User Rights</h5>
                    <p>
                        Zgodnie z RODO, przysługują Państwu następujące prawa:
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Prawo dostępu do swoich danych osobowych (art. 15 RODO)</li>
                        <li>Prawo do sprostowania danych (art. 16 RODO)</li>
                        <li>Prawo do usunięcia danych (art. 17 RODO)</li>
                        <li>Prawo do ograniczenia przetwarzania (art. 18 RODO)</li>
                        <li>Prawo do przenoszenia danych (art. 20 RODO)</li>
                        <li>Prawo do sprzeciwu wobec przetwarzania (art. 21 RODO)</li>
                        <li>Prawo do cofnięcia zgody w dowolnym momencie</li>
                        <li>Prawo do wniesienia skargi do Prezesa UODO</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h5 class="mt-4">Organ Nadzorczy / Supervisory Authority</h5>
                    <p>
                        Przysługuje Państwu prawo wniesienia skargi do Prezesa Urzędu Ochrony Danych Osobowych (PUODO):
                    </p>
                    <ul class="list-unstyled">
                        <li>Urząd Ochrony Danych Osobowych</li>
                        <li>ul. Stawki 2, 00-193 Warszawa</li>
                        <li>Telefon: +48 22 531 03 00</li>
                        <li>E-mail: kancelaria@uodo.gov.pl</li>
                        <li>Strona: <a href="https://uodo.gov.pl" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">uodo.gov.pl</a></li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="alert alert-info mt-5">
                <h5 class="alert-heading">
                    <i class="bi bi-info-circle"></i> Summary
                </h5>
                <p class="mb-0">
                    We are committed to protecting your privacy and complying with GDPR and RODO regulations.
                    Your data is used solely for providing LARP event management services, and you maintain full
                    control over your personal information with the right to access, modify, or delete it at any time.
                    For questions or to exercise your rights, contact us at
                    <a href="mailto:admin@larpilot.com" class="alert-link">admin@larpilot.com</a>.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="text-center mt-5 mb-3">
                <a href="{{ path('backoffice_dashboard') }}" class="btn btn-primary">Return to Dashboard</a>
                <a href="{{ path('terms') }}" class="btn btn-outline-secondary">View Terms of Service</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
